The Kebbi State Police Command has apprehended three persons over counterfeited new naira notes. The trio were caught with notes worth N17 million, according to the Commissioner of Police, Ahmed Magaji Kotangora. They are Faruku Zubair, Ibrahim Musa and Salisu Mohammed of Gungun Tawaye and Chupamini villages in Ngaski Local Government Area. Kotangora disclosed the suspects were nabbed at Warrah Motor Park also within Ngaski LGA. Police officers attached to Warrah Police Station were assisted by National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW) members. The CP confirmed an investigation has been completed, adding that the men will be charged to court for prosecution.